javax.constraints
Interface ReversibleAction

public interface ReversibleAction

This interface represents application-specific actions that can be added during the search and executed during backtracking. For example, an application may draw a square during the search and erase it (a reversible action) during backtracking. This is just a placeholder - this interface will be extended.
